
There are many software tools and frameworks available for creating RESTful APIs. Here are some popular options:

Node.js with Express: Node.js is a popular JavaScript runtime that can be used to build server-side applications, and Express is a lightweight framework that provides tools for building RESTful APIs. Together, they offer a powerful platform for building scalable and efficient APIs.

Python with Flask or Django: Python is a widely used programming language that is well-suited for building web applications, and Flask and Django are two popular web frameworks that can be used to create RESTful APIs. Flask is lightweight and easy to use, while Django is more feature-rich and includes many built-in tools for building web applications.

Ruby on Rails: Ruby on Rails is a popular web application framework that can be used to build RESTful APIs. It offers many built-in tools and conventions for building web applications quickly and efficiently.

Java with Spring: Java is a widely used programming language that is well-suited for building large-scale applications, and Spring is a popular framework that provides tools for building RESTful APIs. It offers many features for handling HTTP requests and responses, as well as support for data persistence, security, and more.

PHP with Laravel: PHP is a popular scripting language that is often used for building web applications, and Laravel is a popular framework that can be used to create RESTful APIs. It offers many built-in tools and features for handling HTTP requests and responses, as well as support for data validation, authentication, and more.

Overall, there are many software tools and frameworks available for creating RESTful APIs, and the choice of tool or framework will depend on factors such as the programming language and development environment, the requirements of the API, and the preferences of the development team.
